question_title: Will the interest in “fafo” change between 2026-02-02 and 2026-02-15 according to Google Trends?
summary: Google Trends term "fafo" is politically active, used by Trump administration and Republican politicians. Currently at level 26 (moderate baseline). The State of the Union is scheduled for Feb 24, AFTER the Feb 2-15 resolution window, so no major spike catalyst is scheduled. However, ongoing political news (government shutdown, immigration) could trigger usage. The ±3 threshold is relatively narrow for a 13-day period with a politically charged term. I estimate moderate probability of stability with slightly higher chance of increase than decrease due to active political use.

factors.description: Active political use by Trump administration - official White House X account posted FAFO Jan 3, 2026; term associated with administration's 'FAFO Presidency' rhetoric
State of the Union Feb 24 is AFTER resolution window - no major scheduled speech event to drive spike
Ongoing political news (government shutdown, immigration crackdown) provides context for FAFO usage
Moderate baseline (26) with ±3 threshold - relatively narrow band for 13-day period, suggests higher probability of crossing threshold
Nothing Ever Happens principle - without specific catalyst, political terms tend toward stability
